Vera Maresova confessed to killing five women and one man over a four-year period at a hospital in Rumburk - a small town in the Czech Republic . 
  She was initially arrested over the death of a 70-year-old woman last August . 
  But has now admitted killing five more people between 2010 and 2014 following a police investigation . 
  Dubbed 'Nurse Death', she injected potassium straight into the blood stream of her elderly patients . 
  All of her victims were already in the intensive care unit at the hospital . 
 